						</p -->
						<P>
						 In 2026, it seems like it should be possible for users to manage their own data
						  through technology. 
						 Business owners would benefit from this as well. 
						</P>
						<P>
						A system where businesses and individuals can both be 
						 assured that submitted data 
						 is real without having to expend capital on fraud detection. 
						 and real people from bots and fake accounts easily and cheaply.
							 <br/><br/>
						 For now, I am calling it "Anonymous Verified Users". 

						 
						 <br/><br/>It leverages Self Soverign Identity (SSI)
						 with the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/did-1.1/">DID spec</a>, 
						 blockchain ledger, zero knowledge proofs, and any other 
             proof of personhood technology as needed.
						<br/><br/>
						The benefits are:
						 <br/>1. reduce the cost of fraud detection 
						 <br/>2. fine-grain control over UGC
						 <br/>3. ability to analyze user data without exposing it 
						</P>
						<P>Users/consumers
							<ol>Can
							<li>Share data</li>
							<li>Define how long we want to share our data</li>
							<li>Sign our data, in a way that is anonymous and unforgeable</li>
							<li>Retain ownership of our data</li>
							</ol>
						<P>System implimenters
							<ol>Can
								<li>Have proof that data is REAL, not a bot, nor a forgery</li>
								<li>Perform computations on the data, without seeing the raw data</li>
							</ol>

						</P>	
            <P>
            One problem that must be addressed is how to stop anyone with
			      access to the data from coping the data in place.
            <br/>
            The current state of the art is such that if a bad actor copies the data in place,
            the owner is disociated from their data and the thief loses the provenance.
						But Fully Homomorphic Encryption (FHE) and ZKP can lock down the gap.
						</P>
